<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/joh.4.34.niv">John 4:34</a><br />
###Consumer or Contributor?<br />
We are not spiritual <strong>consumers</strong>; we are spiritual <strong>contributors</strong>. The church does not exist for <strong>us</strong>. We are the church, and we exist for the <strong>world</strong>.<br />
<a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/joh.4.31-34.niv">John 4:31-34</a></p>
<ol>
  <li>God calls you to serve <strong>in</strong> His church.<br />
<a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/116/rom.12.6-8.nlt">Romans 12:6-8 NLT</a></li>
  <li>God calls you to serve <strong>as</strong> His church.<br />
<a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/mat.5.14-16.niv">Matthew 5:14-16</a><br />
<em>‚ÄúI see a church where people give more than they receive. Where people serve more than they‚Äôve been served. Where people love more than they‚Äôve been loved. A church passionate about reaching the next generation.‚Äù</em></li>
